    section.slide
      h2 Chrome 77
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/chrome.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Chrome')
      p Released September 17th — 
        a(href='https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2019/09/nic77') Release Notes
        |  (
        a(href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=S8aVB3IfOR4') video
        | )
      h3.star Largest Contentful Paint
      ul
        li Measure render time of the 
          a(href='https://web.dev/largest-contentful-paint/') largest content element
        li Best real-world way to measure user-facing performance
        li Uses the 
          a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/PerformanceEntry')
            span.code PerformanceEntry
          |  event of type 
          span.code largest-contentful-paint

    section.slide
      h2 Chrome 77
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/chrome.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Chrome')
      h3.star Easier Custom Form Components
      ul 
        li New 
          span.code formdata
          |  event for appending custom data on submit
        pre
          code
            | const form = document.querySelector('form');
            | form.addEventListener('formdata', ({formData}) => {
            |   formData.append('my-input', myInputValue);
            | });
        p
          a(href='https://web.dev/more-capable-form-controls/#event-based-api') Learn more

    section.slide
      h2 Chrome 77
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/chrome.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Chrome')
      h3.star Easier Custom Form Components
      ul 
        li New 
          span.code formAssociated
          |  property links custom components to a form
        li You provide the field API like 
          span.code .name
          | , 
          span.code .value
          | , etc.
        pre
          code
            | class MyInput extends HTMLElement {
            |   static formAssociated = true;
            |   get value() { return this.value_; }
            |   ...
            | }
        p
          a(href='https://web.dev/more-capable-form-controls/#defining-a-form-associated-custom-element') Learn more

    section.slide
      h2 Chrome 77
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/chrome.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Chrome')
      h3.star Copy Styles
      ul 
        li Right-click any DOM element and 
          span.code Copy &rarr; Copy styles
        li Copies complete DOM node CSS to the clipboard
        li Very convenient for quick style testing
      p Check out lots of other 
        a(href='https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2019/07/devtools') DevTools improvements


    section.slide
      h2 Firefox 69
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/firefox.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Firefox')
      p Released September 3rd — 
        a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox/Releases/69') Release Notes
      h3.star Massive Privacy Release
      ul
        li Enhanced Tracking Protection (ETP)  
          a(href='https://blog.mozilla.org/blog/2019/09/03/todays-firefox-blocks-third-party-tracking-cookies-and-cryptomining-by-default/') enabled by default
        li Blocks all third-party tracking cookies and cryptominers
        li 
          a(href='https://blog.mozilla.org/firefox/how-to-block-fingerprinting-with-firefox/') Fingerprinting scripts
          |  can be blocked by enabling "Strict Mode"
        li New option to 
          a(href='https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/block-autoplay') block all autoplay media
          |  by default
        li Flash is also now 
          a(href='https://www.zdnet.com/article/mozilla-firefox-69-will-disable-adobe-flash-plugin-by-default/') disabled by default

    section.slide
      h2 Firefox 69
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/firefox.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Firefox')
      h3.star Console improvements
      ul
        li Because of ETP, lots of errors are really common now!
        li The console now groups tracking protection, CORS, and CSP errors
        li Blocked resources are also displayed in the Network panel

    section.slide
      h2 Firefox 69
      img(src='../../shared/resources/images/firefox.png', class='corner-image', width='200px', alt='Firefox')
      h3.star Public class fields
      ul
        li Cleaner, self-documenting public fields enabled
        li No private fields yet though... boo!
      pre
        code
          | class Rectangle {
          |   height = 0;
          |   width;
          |   constructor(height, width) {    
          |     this.height = height;
          |     this.width = width;
          |   }
          | }

    section.slide
